t.x HttpServer. However, I’m concerned about the OAuth2 dependency, which isn't mandatory for core web-client coverage but could affect compilation if not included.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Core Vert.x Web Client coverage is reachable with the normal target dependency and an in-process HTTP server, but 5.0.1 still resolves Netty 4.2.x and needs the same Java 25 native-run system properties already used for 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image runs on JDK 25, ensure the generated test project applies runtime system properties `-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` and `-Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true` for `io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1`; do not leave that workaround guarded only for `5.0.0`. Tests can use an in-process Vert.x `HttpServer` bound to `127.0.0.1` with port `0` for request/response, form, multipart, redirect, cookie/session, and caching coverage.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"`OAuth2WebClient` is part of the public API and its signatures reference the optional `io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2` module; if generated tests intentionally cover OAuth2-specific flows, they may need that optional dependency, but it is not required for meaningful core web-client coverage.\",\n    \"External OAuth2/OpenID discovery examples in the documentation should be avoided unless a local/fake endpoint is used, because no Docker service is otherwise required.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01a9d80ec177e944016a40d0b462848190bcdf8ef2c5b0af9b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 252, "output": 740, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30176, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782632621281, "responseId": "resp_01a9d80ec177e944016a40d0adc1bc8190b083879421a91e8f